Rahim is given an activity by his Maths teacher to find some unique relations between a number and it’s digits. After a good day’s work, he decides to show his findings to his teacher in school the next day. The relation he has found out is pretty simple and is as follows. He takes a number and checks if each digit of that number is a divisor of that number.

Input
The only line in the input contains an integer N where 1<=N<=100000.

Output
The output is either “Valid” or “Invalid”(The digit 0 is a valid divisor of the number)

Example

Input:
1) 234
2) 2048
Output:
1) Invalid
2) Valid
